Image 44 of 44 Take a look at the new Miss Venezeula 1 / 44 Back to Gallery Venezuela chose its beauty queen this month. Mariam Habach Santucci, who is part Italian and part Syrian according to an article from Al Arabiya, took the crown and will be representing Venezuela at the next Miss Universe pageant.
Venezuela has had the second-most Miss Universe winners in history behind the United States. Venezuela has won seven titles in total versus eight won by the U.S. The current Miss Universe title holder is Paulina Vega, from neighboring Colombia.
Take a look at the Miss Venezuela pageant that took place last week in the slideshow above.
